              "WarningsOrContraIndicationDescription": [
                {
                  "LanguageCode": "en",
                  "Value": "ISO symbol, Do not use on inflamed, injured or bleeding skin. If a numb or tingling sensation sets in, remove the bandage immediately and check that it is the right size. Do not wear the bandage for long periods of time (no longer than 2 hours continuously, or 6 hours per day) and not while sleeping. For sensory disorders of the skin, circulatory and lymphatic drainage disorders and skin diseases consult a doctor before use. Do not use the support in combination with other compression products, creams, skin oils, etc. Consult a doctor if you have questions about the injury or if the symptoms persist or worsen. In isolated cases, skin reactions or irritations may occur. If these persist, stop wearing the bandage and consult a doctor if necessary. Discontinue use if if the elasticity of the bandage decreases. Inform the manufacturer and the competent authority about serious incidents."
